            <div class="col-md-10">
              <div>
                Americans eat at least 20 billion burgers a year. Most of those burgers come from animals
                raised on polluting factory-farms that are fed a diet of water-intensive GMO corn and soy.
                Raising vast monocultures of feed uses large amounts of toxic chemicals that pollute our
                water and our bodies. It also generates major greenhouse gas emissions and destroys biodiversity
                that support pollinators and other living creatures. Your challenge is to transform the burger
                into a tool for a better food system by advocating for a better burger. Better for you,
                the environment, farmers and animals. Make a burger (meat or plant-based) with only FLOSN ingredients.
              </div>

